# CV Intelligence Layer — Core Rules

## What this project is
A Python FastAPI middleware between a Hiring Platform (external team) and the existing Semantic Search as a Service API. See `SPEC.md` for full specs.

## Architecture rules (CRITICAL — never violate)
1. Never import from or modify the Semantic Search codebase. All interaction via HTTP through `app/services/search_client.py`
2. All HTTP calls to external services go through dedicated client classes in `app/services/`
3. All LLM prompts live in `prompts/*.md` — loaded at startup, never hardcoded
4. Celery tasks must be idempotent — check state before acting
5. Pydantic v2 validates all external input AND all LLM output
6. Every DB change needs an Alembic migration — no raw DDL
7. The Hiring Platform never calls Semantic Search directly

## Tech stack
- Python 3.11+, FastAPI, uvicorn
- PostgreSQL 16 + JSONB, SQLAlchemy 2.0 async + asyncpg
- Celery + Redis for async pipeline
- PyMuPDF, python-docx, Surya OCR, EasyOCR
- Google Gemini API (default) for extraction/ranking/scoring; optional OpenAI-compatible HTTP for local LLM

## Code style
- Type hints on every function signature
- `async def` for all I/O functions
- Google-style docstrings on public functions
- Imports: stdlib → third-party → local, blank line between groups
- Error format: `{"detail": "msg", "code": "ERROR_CODE"}`
- Structured JSON logging with `cv_id` and `job_id`

## Bilingual (FR/EN)
- Detect language with fasttext before LLM calls
- Include detected language in LLM prompt context
- OCR uses `fra+eng` — never assume English

## Key commands
```bash
uvicorn app.main:app --reload --port 8001
pytest tests/ -v
celery -A app.tasks.celery_app worker --loglevel=info
alembic upgrade head
mypy app/ --ignore-missing-imports
ruff check app/ tests/
```
